docs.abstract: President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election bid sputtered badly as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months but found a small crowd and delivered a disjointed speech.
docs.snippet: President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election bid sputtered badly as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months but found a small crowd and delivered a disjointed speech.
docs.lead_paragraph: TULSA, Okla. — President Trump’s attempt to revive his re-election campaign sputtered badly on Saturday night as he traveled to Tulsa for his first mass rally in months and found a far smaller crowd than his aides had promised him, then delivered a disjointed speech that did not address the multiple crises facing the nation or scandals battering him in Washington.

headline.main: Trump Rally Fizzles as Attendance Falls Short of Campaign’s Expectations
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Plan For a Big Rally Sputters Badly

docs.abstract: Claims about the involvement of anti-fascist activists in protests of racism show the many ways false information spreads inside communities online.
docs.snippet: Claims about the involvement of anti-fascist activists in protests of racism show the many ways false information spreads inside communities online.
docs.lead_paragraph: In recent weeks, as demonstrations against racism spread across the country, residents in at least 41 U.S. cities and towns became alarmed by rumors that the loose collective of anti-fascist activists known as antifa was headed to their area, according to an analysis by The New York Times. In many cases, they contacted their local law enforcement for help.

headline.main: 41 Cities, Many Sources: How False Antifa Rumors Spread Locally
headline.print_headline: Brewing Rumors Of Antifa At Home

docs.abstract: Several institutions are preparing to reopen with an awareness of a new mission as people struggle with loss and unrest.
docs.snippet: Several institutions are preparing to reopen with an awareness of a new mission as people struggle with loss and unrest.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the instructor asked him to describe his life in two words, Walter Enriquez chose carefully: fear and violence. He had spent decades as a policeman in Peru during the bloodiest days of armed conflict between government forces and guerrilla fighters that killed nearly 70,000 people. But he said that nothing could have prepared him for the extreme isolation and loneliness that come with quarantine. Having lost a handful of his friends and neighbors to the coronavirus pandemic, the 75-year-old retiree has turned toward art therapy programs offered by the Queens Museum to improve his mental health.

headline.main: Museums Embrace Art Therapy Techniques for Unsettled Times

docs.abstract: Just weeks after another company was criticized for razing ancient caves in the Pilbara desert, BHP said it would expand an iron ore mine on land that contains rock shelters some 15,000 years old.
docs.snippet: Just weeks after another company was criticized for razing ancient caves in the Pilbara desert, BHP said it would expand an iron ore mine on land that contains rock shelters some 15,000 years old.
docs.lead_paragraph: MELBOURNE, Australia — A giant mining company on Thursday said it would go ahead with destroying at least 40 ancient Indigenous sites in the Pilbara desert in Western Australia, just days after a national outcry over revelations that other archaeological sites in the region had been razed.

headline.main: Mining Firm Plans to Destroy Indigenous Australian Sites, Despite Outcry
headline.print_headline: More Australian Indigenous Sites to Be Lost to Mining
